[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring libFuzzer-driven testing of the Mongoose codebase’s network module, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reported a heap-buffer-overflow in the function `rx_icmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `src/mongoose/src/net_builtin.c` at line [0m[1;36m385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A one-byte read past the end of a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap allocation was observed when processing a fuzzed ICMP packet. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow is triggered through the normal fuzzer entry point [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and manifests consistently under the supplied test [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Manifestation  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The crash is detected by AddressSanitizer as a `heap-buffer-overflow` on read [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat address `[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`, immediately past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte allocated region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x150[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The backtrace shows the overflow occurs in:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at `net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385:18[0m[39m`  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Called by `mg_tcpip_rx` at `net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:897:5[0m[39m`  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Invoked from the fuzz harness in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` at [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:106:5[0m[39m`[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - AddressSanitizer labels the issue as a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte heap-buffer-overflow. This [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that the code reads one byte beyond the legitimate bounds of a [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-allocated buffer.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and Key Findings  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The buffer in question was allocated by the fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`malloc` at [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:95:17[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a size of [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m bytes.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `rx_icmp` assumes the packet buffer contains additional data beyond what was [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated, leading to an out-of-bounds read.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The failure is reproducible under the same conditions [0m[1;39m([0m[39minteractive libFuzzer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrun, `-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, suggesting deterministic behavior for the malformed input.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The sanitizer logs and shadow memory dump confirm that the byte at offset [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaddressable [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fa` redzone[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **ICMP processing in net_builtin.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Review bounds checking before reading packet bytes.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Examine how `pkt->payload` length is interpreted and whether header length [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields are validated.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Packet reception wrapper [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_tcpip_rx`, line [0m[1;36m897[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Trace how the packet length and payload are passed into `rx_icmp`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Fuzz harness allocation logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz.c`, line [0m[1;36m95[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Confirm the intended packet structure and size adjustments match the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpectations in `rx_icmp`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Packet data structures [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt` type[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Inspect size fields and metadata describing the buffer length to ensure they[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malign with actual allocations.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions on root causes or fixes are made here. This report highlights the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow symptom, its location in the code, and areas requiring further inspection [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor a complete understanding of the issue.[0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mShadow byte legend [0m[1;39m([0m[39mone shadow byte represents [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m application bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Heap left redzone:       fa[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpefsrull9[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered in the `rx_icmp` function of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/net_builtin.c` when fuzzing the ICMP packet handling path. The overflow occurs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon a one-byte read just past the end of a dynamically allocated buffer [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The patch attempt adds checks to clamp the reply payload length [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`plen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m based on both transmit buffer space and the original packet’s raw buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds. Despite these additions, the overflow persists at the same location in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rx_icmp`, indicating that the new boundary checks did not fully prevent [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds reads.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocates a packet buffer via `malloc` in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe test harness, then invokes `mg_tcpip_rx`, which eventually calls `rx_icmp`.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `rx_icmp`, for ICMP echo requests [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtype [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code computes header overhead [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`hlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and available transmit space [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`space`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then sets payload length `plen = [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpkt->pay.len` clamped to `space`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- An AddressSanitizer report shows a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read just past the end of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion. The problematic read is at:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  … [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m somewhere after these lines, code reads from pkt->pay.buf + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen−[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is reported at `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mnet_builtin.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`rx_icmp`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the buffer `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m150[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and a read at `[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m172[0m[39m`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The OOB read is on the `pkt->pay.buf` region derived from the fuzzer’s raw packet[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer was allocated with length `pkt->raw.len == [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m` but `pkt->pay.len` can [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexceed the remaining space in that buffer.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash trace consistently points to the same line in `rx_icmp` despite varying[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseeds.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch context [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m382[0m[39m of `src/net_builtin.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m static void [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen, plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Limit reply payload to available rx buffer and tx capacity *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Clamp to original payload memory bounds *[0m[35m/[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t raw_offset = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->pay.buf - pkt->raw.buf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw_offset > pkt->raw.len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t avail = pkt->raw.len - raw_offset;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > avail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = avail;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch introduces `raw_offset` to compute how far into the raw buffer the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpayload buffer starts.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It checks if `raw_offset` exceeds `pkt->raw.len`, and returns early if so.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It then limits `plen` by both `avail` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes remaining in the raw buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`space` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes available in the transmit buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Patch[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer log after applying the patch still reports the same AddressSanitizer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at `[0m[35m/src/[0m[95mnet_builtin.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m`.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The faulty read address, allocation details, and backtrace are unchanged, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the conditional returns and clamps did not cover the failing case.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow remains a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read at exactly the same buffer boundary.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and address the overflow, the following parts of the codebase [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarrant closer examination:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **pkt Structure and Initialization**  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – How `pkt->raw.buf`, `pkt->raw.len`, `pkt->pay.buf`, and `pkt->pay.len` are set[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mup in the packet parsing routines.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Whether `pkt->pay.buf` can point outside `pkt->raw.buf` or if its length is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mever inconsistent with `pkt->raw.len`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Buffer Offset Computation**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Whether `raw_offset` calculation correctly reflects the in-buffer offset for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall packet layouts [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., when headers are stripped or aligned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Possible integer underflow or signed/unsigned mismatches when computing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Transmit Buffer Space Calculation**  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Validation of `ifp->tx.len` as the total capacity of the transmit buffer.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Interaction between header overhead [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`hlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and payload length clamping.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Control Flow in `rx_icmp`**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – All code paths that lead to reads from `pkt->pay.buf`. Ensure that each path [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforces a bounds check before accessing payload data.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Behavior when `pkt->icmp->type` is not [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m or when `pkt->ip` fields are invalid.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy reviewing these areas, one can get a holistic view of how packet data is managed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand where the boundary checks break down.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mfuzz[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ shift[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -v TESTCASE [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mTESTCASE[0m[39m=[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -f [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ export [0m[33mSKIP_SEED_CORPUS[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m1[0m                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone-byte read past the end of an allocated buffer. The patch attempt introduces [0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the transmit buffer capacity [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ifp->tx.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying this patch, the same heap-buffer-overflow is still reported at the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation and under the same conditions, indicating the checks did not prevent the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read for the tested input.[0m                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when parsing or copying the ICMP payload.[0m               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs at line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m in `rx_icmp`, where `pkt->pay.buf` is read [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout sufficient bounds checks.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocated region size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m34[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m differs from the payload length [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->pay.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, permitting out-of-bounds access.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This issue bypasses earlier checks for packet type, interface match, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mminimum header size.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original lines around [0m[1;36m383[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m387[0m[39m:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen, plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patched version:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Clamp payload to raw buffer bounds *[0m[35m/[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ptrdiff_t raw_off = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->pay.buf - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->raw.buf;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw_off < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off >= pkt->raw.len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t avail = pkt->raw.len - [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > avail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = avail;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Skip zero-length payload *[0m[35m/[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Clamp to tx buffer capacity *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     struct ip *ip = [0m[1;35mtx_ip[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch introduces:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Computation of `raw_off` to find payload offset in `pkt->raw.buf`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · A check that aborts if `raw_off` is negative or beyond `pkt->raw.len`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Clamping `plen` to the available bytes in `pkt->raw`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · A guard to skip zero-length payloads.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · The existing clamp against transmit‐buffer space is preserved.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Running the same fuzzer input still triggers the identical AddressSanitizer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The log shows the same out-of-bounds read at offset [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte buffer and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same call trace.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that for the test case in question, either the new checks are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot executed/are bypassed or `pkt->pay.buf` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `pkt->raw.buf` relationships differ [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom assumptions in the patch.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The layout and initialization of `pkt->raw.buf`, `pkt->raw.len`, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->pay.buf`, and `pkt->pay.len`—ensure they match the assumptions used in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclamping logic.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other code paths in `rx_icmp` or in upstream functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_tcpip_rx`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanipulate or reassign `pkt->pay.buf` without updating offsets.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Interaction between header parsing, the `eth`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`ip`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`icmp` structures, and the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraw buffer pointer arithmetic.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any alternate branches in `rx_icmp` that read payload bytes outside the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded section.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness behavior in `test/fuzz.c` around buffer allocation [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`malloc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and packet construction to identify why the computed `raw_off` check [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes not prevent the overflow.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            uint8_t ihl = pkt->ip->ver & [0m[1;36m0xF[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mihl < [0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;              [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Invalid IP header length *[0m[35m/[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            size_t ip_header_len = ihl * [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            size_t hlen = eth_len + ip_header_len + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mifp->tx.len < hlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Not enough TX space *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Bounds-check payload pointer and length *[0m[35m/[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            ptrdiff_t raw_off = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->pay.buf - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->raw.buf;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw_off < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off >= pkt->raw.len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was reported in the function `rx_icmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/net_builtin.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when fuzzing the ICMP handling path. The error shows a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread just past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte allocated region backing the packet payload. A patch was [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted adding explicit header‐length calculations, IP header validation, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mraw‐buffer offset and bounds checks, zero‐length payload early return, and payload [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclamping to the transmit buffer. After applying the patch, the fuzzer still [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggers the same heap‐buffer‐overflow at the same location in `rx_icmp`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer, driving `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in mongoose/test/fuzz.c, invokes [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_tcpip_rx` which calls `rx_icmp`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read overflow at src/net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`rx_icmp`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reading from `pkt->pay.buf` beyond the end of its allocated backing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace shows allocation of the packet buffer via `malloc` in the fuzz [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentrypoint, then the overflow occurs when the code processes the payload.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Shadow memory indicates the read access is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `rx_icmp`, the original code computed a fixed header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39meth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and then clamped the payload length only against [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable TX buffer space, without validating the input buffer.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch replaces that logic with:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Extraction of Ethernet length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`eth_len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Derivation of IP header length from `pkt->ip->ver` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIHL field[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and early return[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif invalid [0m[1;39m([0m[39m<[0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Computation of `hlen = eth_len + ip_header_len + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and return if [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe TX buffer is smaller than `hlen`  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Calculation of the raw‐buffer offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`raw_off`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m between `pkt->pay.buf` and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->raw.buf`, with bounds checks to ensure `raw_off` is within `pkt->raw.len`  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Computation of available payload [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`avail = pkt->raw.len - raw_off`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, early [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn on zero payload, then clamping of `plen` to both available raw data and TX [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer space  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch context around line [0m[1;36m382[0m[39m in net_builtin.c:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  static void [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Compute header lengths *[0m[35m/[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t eth_len = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        uint8_t ihl = pkt->ip->ver & [0m[1;36m0xF[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mihl < [0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t ip_header_len = ihl * [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t hlen = eth_len + ip_header_len + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mifp->tx.len < hlen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Bounds‐check payload against raw buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ptrdiff_t raw_off = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->pay.buf - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->raw.buf;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw_off < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off > pkt->raw.len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        size_t avail = pkt->raw.len - [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > avail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = avail;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Skip zero‐length payload *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Clamp to transmit buffer capacity *[0m[35m/[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    struct ip *ip = [0m[1;35mtx_ip[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and rerunning the same fuzz testcase [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times, AddressSanitizer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreports the identical heap-buffer-overflow at the same source location in [0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpefsrull9[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer + AddressSanitizer run on Mongoose’s `rx_icmp` handler triggered a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte heap-buffer-overflow. The initial log shows `rx_icmp` reading one byte past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap allocation. A patch attempt added bounds checks around [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEthernet/IP/ICMP header lengths, validated the raw buffer and payload offsets, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimited the payload copy to available space. Despite these checks, the same [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at `net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385:18[0m[39m` is still reproducible under fuzz [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtesting.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During fuzzing, `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if*, struct pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` reads one byte beyond[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of a heap buffer allocated for `pkt->raw.buf`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports the overflow at line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m in `src/net_builtin.c`, showing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address `[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • That address is [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte region `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x504000000150[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace flows from `rx_icmp` → `mg_tcpip_rx` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming the fuzzer entry point is not the root cause but exercises `rx_icmp`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow occurs before any payload copy or checksum calculation—on initial [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield access in `rx_icmp`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The packet is allocated in the fuzz harness via `[0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->raw.len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, where [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->raw.len` may be too small for header reads in `rx_icmp`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash log repeatedly shows the same frame and allocation site, indicating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeterministic repro.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced a check that `pkt->raw.len` is at least `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39meth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validated the IP header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ihl`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is ≥[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m and computed `ip_header_len = ihl * [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensured transmit buffer `ifp->tx.len` can hold headers + payload.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Computed and bounded `raw_off` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe offset of the payload buffer within [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`raw.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adjusted `pkt->pay.len` to fit within `pkt->raw.len - raw_off`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Rebased `pkt->pay.buf` and guarded against zero-length payload.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Performed `memcpy` of payload only after these checks.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After applying the patch, fuzzing still aborts with the same AddressSanitizer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror at `net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385:18[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow remains in the same location, indicating that the initial guard [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->icmp->type` or header reads[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is still triggered on undersized [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->raw.len`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code that sets up `pkt->raw.len`, `pkt->icmp`, `pkt->ip`, and `pkt->pay` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore calling `rx_icmp`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definition and initialization of `struct pkt` fields in `net_builtin.c` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`test/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How `[0m[1;35mtx_ip[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` derives and positions the ICMP header pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`struct icmp *icmp =[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mip + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any assumptions about contiguous layout of `eth`, `ip`, `icmp`, and `pay` buffers[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin `pkt->raw.buf`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interaction between the `ver` field in `struct ip` and actual buffer length.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
